					<dd class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-18698">
<p>Hi Kate, Glad you found this helpful. Just a hint, you may want to keep the credit cards or bank accounts open just do not use them so long as there are no monthly maintenance fees or annual fees on the cards. Having untapped lines of credit is always handy and may help your FICO score, if you even care about it (I do not). Having extra bank accounts open is also helpful just in case you may need to use them in the future for whatever reason. So long as the amount in them is fairly immaterial, like $100, and so long as there are no maintenance fees then there is not much to lose and the deposits may actually be a loss for the bank (if they print and mail a statement each month &#8230;. which is not very green).</p>
<p>Where I really like to starve the vampire squid is with its media properties. For example, I have not had cable television in over a decade. Also, Newsweek, the entire company, just sold for $1. So, I would look for ways to starve the vampire squid of your time, attention and then money. Likely you will be happier also if you are not being programmed by their programming.</p>
